Addition and multiplication of Integers:

        int x= 10;
        int y= 15;
        int sum = x + y;
        System.out.println("sum of "+ x + " and sum of " + y + " is = " + sum);
        // xy
        int prd = x * y;
        System.out.println("product of "+ x + " and sum of " + y + " is = " + prd);


>>>> 
sum of 10 and sum of 15 is = 25
product of 10 and sum of 15 is = 150



#Machine Rule is not BODMAS:
Machine Rule is LEFT TO RIGHT + BODMAS:

        //exp
        int exp = x * y / x + y;
        System.out.println(exp);
        //correct way of doing exp
        int expr = (x * y) / (x + y);
        System.out.println(expr);

>>>
30
6

##So, if you want answer in a perticular way you should place BRACKET.



IF and ELSE:

    int x = 11;
    if (x % 2 == 0)
    {
        System.out.println(x +" is Even");
    }
    else
    {
        System.out.println(x +" is odd.");
    }
    
    System.out.println("Harwork and Hardwork");


>>>
11 is odd.
Harwork and Hardwork


## if me bhi semi colon nahi lagega aur else me bhi semi colon nahi lagega.


###check MAX and MIN  with IF and ELSE;

    int x = 10;
    int y = 2;
    
    if (x == y)
    {
        System.out.println(x + " is equal to "+ y);
    }
    else
    {
        if(x > y)
        {
            System.out.println(x +" is greater than " + y);
        }
        else
        {
            System.out.println(y +" is greater than " + x);
        }
    }
    
>>>>>
10 is greater than 2




###check MAX and MIN  with else if;



    int x = 10;
    int y = 12;
    
    if (x == y)
    {
        System.out.println(x + " is equal to "+ y);
    }
    else if (x > y)
    {
        System.out.println(x +" is greater than " + y);
    }
    
    else
    {
        System.out.println(y +" is greater than " + x);
    }
   

>>>>
12 is greater than 10


###Marks Grading System:

    if(marks > 90)
    {
        System.out.println("excellent");
    }
    else if(marks > 80 && marks <= 90)
    {
        System.out.println("good");
    }
    else if(marks > 70 && marks <= 80)
    {
        System.out.println("fair");
    }
    else if(marks > 60 && marks <= 70)
  {
      System.out.println("meets expectations");
  }
  else
  {
      System.out.println("below par");
  }




###While Loop:

3 steps will always present in a While loop:

    1. Initialization.
    2. Evaluataion.
    3. Increment.


  	    int i=1;
		while(i<=10)	
		{
			System.out.println(i);
			i++;
		}
		System.out.println("Done");




###For Loop:

    for(int i = 1; i <= 10; i++)
    {
      System.out.println(i);
    }

for loop take 3 steps in only and only in following order:

    1. Check
    2. body
    3. Increment.



Taking Input:


Integer:


      Scanner scn=new Scanner(System.in);
      int n= scn.nextInt();  
      for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++)
      {
        System.out.println(i);
      }


String:

      Scanner scn=new Scanner(System.in);
      String name= scn.nextLine();  
      
      System.out.println("Hello " + name + "!");


##For both Integer and String input in a single program:

      Scanner scn=new Scanner(System.in);
      int n = Integer.parseInt(scn.nextLine());
      String name= scn.nextLine();  
      
      System.out.println("Hello " + name + "! Here is your counting.");
      for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++)
      {
        System.out.println(i);
      }


Prime Numbers: Wo number jo khud se aur 1 se divide hote hai. jaise 7, 11, 17


